in faint chirping♪

237
00:17:12,870 --> 00:17:14,910
♪Mist covering someone's eyes♪

238
00:17:15,030 --> 00:17:18,630
♪Like a dream yet to awaken♪

239
00:17:20,830 --> 00:17:23,670
♪It's supposed to be marvelous scenes♪

240
00:17:23,870 --> 00:17:27,030
♪Traveling alone only to witness♪

241
00:17:27,150 --> 00:17:29,150
♪The changes of the world♪

242
00:17:29,950 --> 00:17:31,630
♪Until a red maple leaf♪

243
00:17:32,110 --> 00:17:33,870
♪Lingers in the past♪

244
00:17:34,230 --> 00:17:37,350
♪That reminds people of romance♪

245
00:17:38,710 --> 00:17:39,270
Thank you for your patience.

246
00:17:39,300 --> 00:17:41,870
♪The joy and sorrow are like ephemerals♪

247
00:17:42,350 --> 00:17:44,990
♪Silently passing by each other♪

248
00:17:45,310 --> 00:17:45,960
What's the matter?

249
00:17:45,980 --> 00:17:47,500
♪With a glimpse♪

250
00:17:47,510 --> 00:17:49,030
Nothing.

251
00:17:49,060 --> 00:17:50,500
